Kensho Suzuki

  • Assume a population has three statuses, A,B, and C. Set a transition matrix M that moves some fraction of each status to other statuses. Simulate the change of fraction per status.
  • Draw a graph whose nodes are statuses and edges are transition among them. Make the size of vertices proportional to the fraction in the population at a particular point. Make the width of edges proportional to the probability in transition.

Assume a population has three statuses, A,B, and C. Set a transition matrix M that moves some fraction of each status to other statuses. Simulate the change of fraction per status.

init.S <- c(300, 700, 500)
M <- matrix(c(0.6,0.2,0.2,0.4,0.2,0.4,0.2,0.6,0.2),3,3)
n <- 20
SS <- matrix(0,n,3)
SS[1,] <- init.S
for(i in 2:n){
    SS[i,] <- M %*% SS[i-1,]
}
matplot(SS, type="l")

Draw a graph whose nodes are statuses and edges are transition among them. Make the size of vertices proportional to the fraction in the population at a particular point. Make the width of edges proportional to the probability in transition.

n = 1
g1 <- graph.adjacency(M, mode="directed", weighted=TRUE)
V(g1)$name <- c('A', 'B', 'C')
E(g1)$curved <- TRUE

V(g1)$weight <- init.S
plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)

n = 2
V(g1)$weight <- SS[2,]
plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)

n = 3
V(g1)$weight <- SS[3,]
plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)

n = 5
V(g1)$weight <- SS[5,]
plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)

n = 10

plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)

n = 20

plot(g1,vertex.label=V(g1)$name, vertex.size=V(g1)$weight/10, vertex.color=c('red','blue','green'), edge.width=E(g1)$weight*10, edge.label=E(g1)$weight)
